n attacker has full control: file upload\\/delete, command execution, database access.\",\"fix\":\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE REQUIRED:\\n1. Delete the file: rm \\/path\\/to\\/shell.php\\n2. Check all upload directories: find \\/var\\/www -name \'*.php\' -path \'*\\/upload*\'\\n3. Review access logs: grep \'shell.php\' \\/var\\/log\\/apache2\\/access.log\\n4. Change ALL credentials: DB password, FTP, SSH, hosting panel\\n5. Restore from a clean backup if compromise is confirmed\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/c99.php\",\"name\":\"C99 Web Shell Detected\",\"severity\":\"CRITICAL\",\"category\":\"Active Backdoor \\/ Compromise\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"C99 is one of the most widely deployed PHP web shells. It provides attackers with a full file manager, command execution terminal, database browser, network scanner, and privilege escalation tools. Server is likely fully compromised.\",\"fix\":\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE \\u2014 Server is likely compromised:\\n1. rm \\/path\\/to\\/c99.php\\n2. find \\/var\\/www -name \'c99*.php\' -delete\\n3. Isolate server from network if possible\\n4. Audit all PHP files: grep -r \'eval(base64_decode\' \\/var\\/www\\/\\n5. Change ALL credentials immediately\\n6. File a security incident report\\n7. Restore from pre-infection backup\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/r57.php\",\"name\":\"R57 Web Shell Detected\",\"severity\":\"CRITICAL\",\"category\":\"Active Backdoor \\/ Compromise\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"R57 is a PHP web shell providing full server control: file operations, command execution, FTP brute-forcing, SQL database access, and port scanning. Presence strongly indicates server compromise.\",\"fix\":\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE:\\n1. rm \\/path\\/to\\/r57.php\\n2. find \\/var\\/www -name \'r57*.php\' -delete\\n3. Full forensic audit required\\n4. grep -r \'c99\\\\|r57\\\\|b374k\\\\|wso\\\\|shell\' \\/var\\/www\\/ --include=\'*.php\' -l\\n5. Change all credentials and API keys\\n6. Contact your hosting provider\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/b374k.php\",\"name\":\"B374K Web Shell Detected\",\"severity\":\"CRITICAL\",\"category\":\"Active Backdoor \\/ Compromise\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"B374K is a sophisticated PHP web shell with file management, terminal emulation, encoded command execution, database tools, and network utilities. Considered a professional-grade attacker tool.\",\"fix\":\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE:\\n1. rm \\/path\\/to\\/b374k.php\\n2. Find all web shells: grep -r \'eval(base64_decode\\\\|gzinflate\\\\|str_rot13\' \\/var\\/www\\/ --include=\'*.php\' -l\\n3. Take server offline if data breach is suspected\\n4. Restore from clean backup\\n5. Change all passwords, API keys, DB credentials\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/wso.php\",\"name\":\"WSO Web Shell Detected\",\"severity\":\"CRITICAL\",\"category\":\"Active Backdoor \\/ Compromise\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"WSO (Web Shell by Orb) provides attackers complete server control with file manager, terminal, database browser, and mass defacement tools. Extremely common in CMS-based compromises.\",\"fix\":\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE:\\n1. Delete: rm \\/path\\/to\\/wso.php\\n2. Scan: find \\/var\\/www -name \'wso*.php\' -o -name \'*.ph\' -o -name \'*.phtml\' 2>\\/dev\\/null\\n3. Audit access logs for POST requests to PHP files in upload dirs\\n4. This server must be treated as FULLY COMPROMISED\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/xmlrpc.php\",\"name\":\"XML-RPC Endpoint Exposed\",\"severity\":\"HIGH\",\"category\":\"Brute Force \\/ DDoS Amplification\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"WordPress XML-RPC is publicly accessible. Attackers use it to attempt thousands of login combinations in a single request (credential stuffing) and to amplify DDoS attacks via pingback. This is one of the most actively exploited WordPress endpoints.\",\"fix\":\"# Apache \\u2014 add to .htaccess or VirtualHost:\\n<Files xmlrpc.php>\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n<\\/Files>\\n\\n# Nginx \\u2014 add to server block:\\nlocation = \\/xmlrpc.php {\\n  deny all;\\n  return 403;\\n}\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/timthumb.php\",\"name\":\"TimThumb Script Detected\",\"severity\":\"HIGH\",\"category\":\"Known Vulnerable Script\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"TimThumb is a deprecated image-resizing script with critical remote code execution vulnerabilities (CVE-2011-4106, CVE-2014-4663). Its presence indicates the site uses old themes or plugins. Attackers actively scan for this file.\",\"fix\":\"# Immediate action \\u2014 delete the file:\\nrm \\/path\\/to\\/timthumb.php\\n\\n# Then update ALL WordPress themes and plugins.\\n# Find all copies: find \\/var\\/www -name \'timthumb.php\' 2>\\/dev\\/null\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/php-cgi\\/php.cgi\",\"name\":\"PHP-CGI Binary Exposed (CVE-2012-1823)\",\"severity\":\"HIGH\",\"category\":\"Remote Code Execution Path\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"A PHP-CGI binary is web-accessible. CVE-2012-1823 allows attackers to pass command-line options via the query string, enabling remote code execution. This vulnerability is over 10 years old but still actively scanned.\",\"fix\":\"# Apache \\u2014 block php.cgi in config:\\n<Files php.cgi>\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n<\\/Files>\\n\\n# Switch to PHP-FPM (mod_fastcgi or mod_proxy_fcgi) instead of CGI mode.\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"php.ini \\u2192 disable_functions\",\"name\":\"OS Command Functions Not Disabled\",\"severity\":\"HIGH\",\"category\":\"Code Execution Amplifier\",\"http_code\":null,\"description\":\"The following PHP functions can execute OS commands and are NOT disabled: exec, system, passthru, shell_exec, popen, proc_open. If an attacker achieves any code execution (via file upload, injection, or deserialization), these functions allow full server takeover \\u2014 listing files, exfiltrating data, installing backdoors.\",\"fix\":\"# Add to php.ini (then restart PHP-FPM \\/ Apache):\\ndisable_functions = exec,system,passthru,shell_exec,popen,proc_open,pclose,pcntl_exec\\n\\n# Verify it applied:\\nphp -r \\\"var_dump(function_exists(\'exec\'));\\\" \\/\\/ should print bool(false)\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/wp-login.php\",\"name\":\"WordPress Login Page Exposed\",\"severity\":\"MEDIUM\",\"category\":\"Brute Force Entry Point\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"The WordPress login page is publicly reachable without any rate limiting or IP restriction. Automated bots continuously attempt credential stuffing attacks against this endpoint. A successful attack leads to full admin takeover.\",\"fix\":\"# Apache \\u2014 restrict to your office\\/home IP:\\n<Files wp-login.php>\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n  Allow from YOUR.IP.ADDRESS\\n<\\/Files>\\n\\n# OR install a CAPTCHA + 2FA plugin (Wordfence, WP-Cerber).\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/wp-admin\\/\",\"name\":\"WordPress Admin Panel Exposed\",\"severity\":\"MEDIUM\",\"category\":\"Admin Panel Exposure\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"The WordPress admin area is accessible from any IP. Beyond brute force, this exposes admin AJAX endpoints used by many plugins, some of which have had unauthenticated vulnerability disclosures.\",\"fix\":\"# Apache \\u2014 restrict \\/wp-admin\\/ to your IP:\\n<Directory \\\"\\/var\\/www\\/html\\/wp-admin\\\">\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n  Allow from YOUR.IP.ADDRESS\\n<\\/Directory>\\n\\n# Also rename \\/wp-admin\\/ via a security plugin like WPS Hide Login.\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/administrator\\/\",\"name\":\"Joomla Admin Panel Exposed\",\"severity\":\"MEDIUM\",\"category\":\"Admin Panel Exposure\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"The Joomla administrator panel is publicly accessible. Automated scanners actively target this URL for brute-force attacks and known CVE exploitation.\",\"fix\":\"# Apache \\u2014 restrict to your IP:\\n<Directory \\\"\\/var\\/www\\/html\\/administrator\\\">\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n  Allow from YOUR.IP.ADDRESS\\n<\\/Directory>\\n\\n# Joomla: Admin Tools Pro \\u2192 .htaccess Maker \\u2192 IP-protect \\/administrator\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"\\/cgi-bin\\/\",\"name\":\"CGI Directory Publicly Accessible\",\"severity\":\"MEDIUM\",\"category\":\"Script Execution Risk\",\"http_code\":301,\"description\":\"The CGI directory is web-accessible. CGI scripts (particularly old Perl\\/Shell scripts) are frequently targeted for code injection and often contain vulnerabilities like Shellshock (CVE-2014-6271).\",\"fix\":\"# Apache \\u2014 disable CGI if not needed:\\na2dismod cgi\\n\\n# Or restrict access:\\n<Directory \\\"\\/var\\/www\\/cgi-bin\\\">\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n<\\/Directory>\\n\\n# Review all CGI scripts for injection vulnerabilities.\",\"accessible\":true},{\"path\":\"php.ini \\u2192 allow_url_fopen\",\"name\":\"allow_url_fopen Enabled (SSRF \\/ RFI Risk)\",\"severity\":\"MEDIUM\",\"category\":\"Remote File Inclusion \\/ SSRF\",\"http_code\":null,\"description\":\"allow_url_fopen=On permits PHP file functions (file_get_contents, include, require) to fetch remote URLs. If any user input reaches these functions without validation, attackers can: (1) include malicious remote PHP code (RFI), (2) probe internal services (SSRF), (3) exfiltrate data to external endpoints.\",\"fix\":\"# php.ini:\\nallow_url_fopen = Off\\n\\n# If your app needs remote HTTP: use cURL instead (gives proper security controls):\\n$ch = curl_init(\'https:\\/\\/example.com\\/data.json\');\\ncurl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);\\n\\/\\/ add CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER, timeout, etc.\\n$body = curl_exec($ch);\",\"accessible\":true}],\"summary\":{\"critical\":6,\"high\":4,\"medium\":5,\"low\":0,\"total\":15}},\"https_redirect\":{\"http_code\":301,\"redirects_to_https\":true,\"location\":\"https:\\/\\/productaccess.in\\/\"},\"http_methods\":{\"http_code\":301,\"allowed_methods\":[],\"dangerous\":[]},\"directory_listing\":{\"checked\":[\"\\/images\\/\",\"\\/uploads\\/\",\"\\/backup\\/\",\"\\/files\\/\",\"\\/assets\\/\",\"\\/static\\/\",\"\\/media\\/\",\"\\/logs\\/\"],\"exposed\":[]},\"robots_txt\":{\"available\":true,\"disallowed\":[],\"sensitive_hints\":[]},\"cookie_security\":{\"cookies\":[]},\"email_security\":{\"domain\":\"productaccess.in\",\"spf\":\"v=spf1 include:spf.protection.outlook.com -all\",\"dmarc\":\"v=DMARC1; p=none;\"},\"tech_stack\":[{\"name\":\"Cloudflare\",\"category\":\"CDN\"}],\"risk_level\":\"HIGH\",\"risk_score\":433,\"issues\":[\"[MEDIUM] Port 8080 (HTTP-Alt) is publicly accessible\",\"[MEDIUM] Port 8443 (HTTPS-Alt) is publicly accessible\",\"[MEDIUM] Risky PHP setting enabled: display_errors\",\"[LOW] open_basedir is not configured\",\"[MEDIUM] No dangerous PHP functions are disabled\",\"[LOW] Missing HTTP security header: X-Frame-Options\",\"[LOW] Missing HTTP security header: X-Content-Type-Options\",\"[LOW] Missing HTTP security header: X-XSS-Protection\",\"[LOW] Missing HTTP security header: Strict-Transport-Security\",\"[LOW] Missing HTTP security header: Content-Security-Policy\",\"[LOW] Missing HTTP security header: Referrer-Policy\",\"[LOW] Server software version disclosed in header: cloudflare\",\"[HIGH] World-writable path detected: G:\\/xmp\\/htdocs (perms: 0777)\",\"[HIGH] Suspicious recently modified PHP file detected: constants.php\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.env (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.env.local (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.env.production (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.git\\/HEAD (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.git\\/config (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/phpinfo.php (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/info.php (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/test.php (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/config.php (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.htaccess (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/server-status (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/server-info (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.DS_Store (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/debug.log (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/error.log (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/access.log (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/app.log (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/composer.json (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/composer.lock (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/package.json (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/Dockerfile (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.dockerenv (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/admin\\/ (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/phpmyadmin\\/ (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/adminer.php (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/backup.zip (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/db.sql (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/database.sql (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.ssh\\/id_rsa (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/.bash_history (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] Sensitive path publicly accessible: \\/web.config (HTTP 301)\",\"[HIGH] [Malware Risk] XML-RPC Endpoint Exposed (HTTP 301 on \\/xmlrpc.php)\",\"[MEDIUM] [Malware Risk] WordPress Login Page Exposed (HTTP 301 on \\/wp-login.php)\",\"[MEDIUM] [Malware Risk] WordPress Admin Panel Exposed (HTTP 301 on \\/wp-admin\\/)\",\"[MEDIUM] [Malware Risk] Joomla Admin Panel Exposed (HTTP 301 on \\/administrator\\/)\",\"[HIGH] [Malware Risk] TimThumb Script Detected (HTTP 301 on \\/timthumb.php)\",\"[CRITICAL] [Malware Risk] PHP Eval Endpoint (CVE-2019-11043) (HTTP 301 on \\/eval-stdin.php)\",\"[HIGH] [Malware Risk] PHP-CGI Binary Exposed (CVE-2012-1823) (HTTP 301 on \\/php-cgi\\/php.cgi)\",\"[MEDIUM] [Malware Risk] CGI Directory Publicly Accessible (HTTP 301 on \\/cgi-bin\\/)\",\"[CRITICAL] [Malware Risk] Web Shell Detected: shell.php (HTTP 301 on \\/shell.php)\",\"[CRITICAL] [Malware Risk] C99 Web Shell Detected (HTTP 301 on \\/c99.php)\",\"[CRITICAL] [Malware Risk] R57 Web Shell Detected (HTTP 301 on \\/r57.php)\",\"[CRITICAL] [Malware Risk] B374K Web Shell Detected (HTTP 301 on \\/b374k.php)\",\"[CRITICAL] [Malware Risk] WSO Web Shell Detected (HTTP 301 on \\/wso.php)\",\"[MEDIUM] allow_url_fopen=On \\u2014 enables Remote File Inclusion and Server-Side Request Forgery attacks\"],\"recommendations\":[\"Restrict port 8080 with firewall rules unless required externally\",\"Restrict port 8443 with firewall rules unless required externally\",\"Set display_errors=Off in production to prevent information leakage\",\"Set open_basedir in php.ini to restrict file access to specific directories\",\"Add to php.ini: disable_functions = exec,shell_exec,system,passthru,popen,proc_open\",\"Configure your web server to send the X-Frame-Options response header on all responses\",\"Configure your web server to send the X-Content-Type-Options response header on all responses\",\"Configure your web server to send the X-XSS-Protection response header on all responses\",\"Configure your web server to send the Strict-Transport-Security response header on all responses\",\"Configure your web server to send the Content-Security-Policy response header on all responses\",\"Configure your web server to send the Referrer-Policy response header on all responses\",\"Remove or obfuscate the Server response header to prevent version fingerprinting\",\"Change permissions immediately: chmod 755 G:\\/xmp\\/htdocs\",\"Manually review G:\\/xmp\\/htdocs\\\\eacademy-update\\\\application\\\\config\\\\constants.php \\u2014 it may be a web shell or injected malicious code\",\"Block access to \\/.env via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.env.local via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.env.production via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.git\\/HEAD via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.git\\/config via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/phpinfo.php via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/info.php via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/test.php via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/config.php via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.htaccess via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/server-status via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/server-info via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.DS_Store via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/debug.log via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/error.log via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/access.log via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/app.log via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/composer.json via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/composer.lock via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/package.json via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/Dockerfile via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.dockerenv via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/admin\\/ via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/phpmyadmin\\/ via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/adminer.php via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/backup.zip via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/db.sql via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/database.sql via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.ssh\\/id_rsa via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/.bash_history via web server config or delete the file\",\"Block access to \\/web.config via web server config or delete the file\",\"# Apache \\u2014 add to .htaccess or VirtualHost:\\n<Files xmlrpc.php>\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n<\\/Files>\\n\\n# Nginx \\u2014 add to server block:\\nlocation = \\/xmlrpc.php {\\n  deny all;\\n  return 403;\\n}\",\"# Apache \\u2014 restrict to your office\\/home IP:\\n<Files wp-login.php>\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n  Allow from YOUR.IP.ADDRESS\\n<\\/Files>\\n\\n# OR install a CAPTCHA + 2FA plugin (Wordfence, WP-Cerber).\",\"# Apache \\u2014 restrict \\/wp-admin\\/ to your IP:\\n<Directory \\\"\\/var\\/www\\/html\\/wp-admin\\\">\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n  Allow from YOUR.IP.ADDRESS\\n<\\/Directory>\\n\\n# Also rename \\/wp-admin\\/ via a security \",\"# Apache \\u2014 restrict to your IP:\\n<Directory \\\"\\/var\\/www\\/html\\/administrator\\\">\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n  Allow from YOUR.IP.ADDRESS\\n<\\/Directory>\\n\\n# Joomla: Admin Tools Pro \\u2192 .htaccess Maker \",\"# Immediate action \\u2014 delete the file:\\nrm \\/path\\/to\\/timthumb.php\\n\\n# Then update ALL WordPress themes and plugins.\\n# Find all copies: find \\/var\\/www -name \'timthumb.php\' 2>\\/dev\\/null\",\"# Delete the file:\\nrm \\/path\\/to\\/eval-stdin.php\\n\\n# Upgrade PHP (7.3.11+ \\/ 7.2.24+ \\/ 7.1.33+)\\n# Review php-fpm.conf \\u2014 ensure PATH_INFO is not enabled unnecessarily\\n# Nginx config fix:\\nlocation ~ \\\\.php$\",\"# Apache \\u2014 block php.cgi in config:\\n<Files php.cgi>\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n<\\/Files>\\n\\n# Switch to PHP-FPM (mod_fastcgi or mod_proxy_fcgi) instead of CGI mode.\",\"# Apache \\u2014 disable CGI if not needed:\\na2dismod cgi\\n\\n# Or restrict access:\\n<Directory \\\"\\/var\\/www\\/cgi-bin\\\">\\n  Order deny,allow\\n  Deny from all\\n<\\/Directory>\\n\\n# Review all CGI scripts for injection vulne\",\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE REQUIRED:\\n1. Delete the file: rm \\/path\\/to\\/shell.php\\n2. Check all upload directories: find \\/var\\/www -name \'*.php\' -path \'*\\/upload*\'\\n3. Review access logs: grep \'shell.php\' \\/var\\/log\",\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE \\u2014 Server is likely compromised:\\n1. rm \\/path\\/to\\/c99.php\\n2. find \\/var\\/www -name \'c99*.php\' -delete\\n3. Isolate server from network if possible\\n4. Audit all PHP files: grep -r \'eval\",\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE:\\n1. rm \\/path\\/to\\/r57.php\\n2. find \\/var\\/www -name \'r57*.php\' -delete\\n3. Full forensic audit required\\n4. grep -r \'c99\\\\|r57\\\\|b374k\\\\|wso\\\\|shell\' \\/var\\/www\\/ --include=\'*.php\' -l\\n5. Change\",\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE:\\n1. rm \\/path\\/to\\/b374k.php\\n2. Find all web shells: grep -r \'eval(base64_decode\\\\|gzinflate\\\\|str_rot13\' \\/var\\/www\\/ --include=\'*.php\' -l\\n3. Take server offline if data breach is suspec\",\"# IMMEDIATE RESPONSE:\\n1. Delete: rm \\/path\\/to\\/wso.php\\n2. Scan: find \\/var\\/www -name \'wso*.php\' -o -name \'*.ph\' -o -name \'*.phtml\' 2>\\/dev\\/null\\n3. Audit access logs for POST requests to PHP files in uploa\",\"Set allow_url_fopen=Off in php.ini; replace file_get_contents(URL) calls with cURL\"],\"scanned_at\":\"2026-04-02 04:45:18\"}', 1, '2026-04-02 04:45:18');
